  "prompt": "What's that device on umpire's arm?",
  "response": "The device on an umpire's arm is called an \"umpire's communication system\" or \"PitchCom.\" It's used in baseball to receive signals from the catcher about the type of pitch they want. This device helps to prevent sign-stealing by opposing teams and speeds up the game by reducing the time needed for communication between the catcher and pitcher.",
